year: 1. Some mother's and fathers' ages are unavailable. This means that calculations on these statistics are not wholly representative of all mothers and fathers. In 2016-2020, mother's age was missing from 0.1% of birth certificates

Fathers age was missing from 3.82% of birth certificates. Fathers age can be missing because the fathers details were not on the birth certificate, or because their age was not known to the person registering the birth
year = Year the birth was registered in.
firstname = First name of the baby.
ranking = Where this baby name ranked by popularity by year and sex.
frequency = How many babies had this name by year and sex.
mother_age_mean = The total sum of all mother's ages by firstname and year divided by the number of mothers by firstname and year.
father_age_mean = The total sum of all father's ages by firstname and year divided by the number of fathers by firstname and year.
mother_age_median = The 50th percentile in the age range of mothers by firstname. The exact "midpoint" in the age range.
father_age_median = The 50th percentile in the age range of fathers by firstname. The exact "midpoint" in the age range.
mother_age_stdev = standard deviation in the age range of mothers by firstname and year.
father_age_stdev = standard deviation in the age range of fathers by firstname and year.
